developments were holding lotteries to determine

35
00:02:58,880 --> 00:03:05,460
which buyers would be allowed to purchase!
Shortages result in increasing market prices,

36
00:03:05,460 --> 00:03:09,980
leading to an increase in the quantity supplied,
and a decrease in the quantity demanded. When

37
00:03:09,980 --> 00:03:16,179
will the prices stop rising? When there's
no more pressure -- no more shortage. In short,

38
00:03:16,180 --> 00:03:19,330
the market stabilizes at P1.

39
00:03:19,330 --> 00:03:26,330
Now, fast-forward three years to observe the
Phoenix housing market in 2008. In 2008, prices

40
00:03:26,510 --> 00:03:33,510
